{
  "doc_id": "28570",
  "text": "Evodiamine (EVO), a Chinese herb of the evodia rutaecarpa family, may inhibit cell proliferation and induce apoptosis in cancer cell lines by downregulating B cell lymphoma 2 (Bcl-2), B cell lymphoma extra large (Bcl-xl), caspase-3, caspase-9, and vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF), while upregulating Bcl-2-associated X protein (Bax). [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] Our recent studies have indicated that EVO inhibits cell growth and submit your manuscript | www.dovepress.com",
